Senator Kirsten Gillibrand issued a statement supporting President Obama's proposals to create jobs. She emphasized the need for bold ideas that encourage businesses to hire Americans and unlock the potential of American innovation and hard work. Gillibrand called for Democrats and Republicans to work together to address the job crisis and create new jobs, stating that Americans deserve better from Congress. She stressed the importance of thinking big and having good faith and common purpose from both parties in Congress to create a thriving middle class for the new economy.